  <num>25-804</num>
  <heading>Notifications from DLCP, Fire Department, and Metropolitan Police Department.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>In accordance with procedures that the Mayor shall establish, the Department of Licensing and Consumer Protection, the Office of Tax and Revenue, and the Fire and Emergency Medical Services shall promptly notify the Board if a licensed establishment is the subject of a citation, revocation, or other enforcement action for a violation of laws or regulations enforced by these departments.</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>If a licensed establishment is the subject of an incident report by the Metropolitan Police Department, the Metropolitan Police Department shall file a copy of the incident report with the Board. The Board shall make the report available for public inspection upon request.</text>
  </para>
